SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1049
By Stevens
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Henry County
High School Madrigals upon their victory at the
WorldStrides Festival.
WHEREAS, it is the privilege of the members of this General Assembly to recognize
those young artists who have reached the pinnacle of success while bringing joy to others
through their creative expression and promoting the importance of the performing arts; and
WHEREAS, the Henry County High School Madrigals, performers of extraordinary
talent, skill, and dedication, recently garnered the gold while competing in the WorldStrides
Festival, held at the historic Riverside Church in New York, New York; and
WHEREAS, under the tireless leadership of Director Deanna Brown, the Madrigals
diligently worked on several very challenging festival pieces for months prior to competition; and
WHEREAS, in New York, the Madrigals were awarded a Gold Rating as well as the
Adjudicator Award, which is given to ensembles receiving an average score of 95 or higher; this
follows a Superior Rating achieved at the Senior High Choral Festival in Memphis; and
WHEREAS, the Madrigals' notable achievement is a source of great pride for their
families, their community, and their school; and
WHEREAS, the Henry County High School Madrigals epitomize all that is good in
today's student artists, as they have achieved a high level of success in music performance
while evincing great character both on and off the stage; and
WHEREAS, it is most fitting that we recognize the ever-growing legacy of this
phenomenal group on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Henry County High
